<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_a1e97c83-3ed4-4d4f-8083-86b5ccb68ed4" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>13.4.2</sptc><title id="_3660a999-7894-4e88-96ac-3371590fc31a">Chimneys and flues</title><archive-num>2019: 3.12.3.1</archive-num><subclause id="_6247e8ac-ae1b-438c-980f-add247ba41cd" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_9e867901-0d56-4a48-8b7c-008b944eb84f">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The chimney or flue of an open solid-fuel burning appliance must be provided with a damper or flap that can be closed to seal the chimney or flue.</p></subclause><callout id="_9d8a3c1e-5428-41db-8957-64112e7c5940"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><ul outputclass="numbered"><li>The requirements of this Part are to be read in conjunction with the fire safety requirements in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/4230_0.6.0.xml#_99ae28ad-343e-4437-8c1c-0cf518f9c6bd" id="_f4c46a6f-d8e6-4e94-8505-d1a26c88e7e9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 12.4</xref> of the ABCB Housing Provisions.</li><li>A solid-fuel burning appliance is a heater that burns materials such as timber, coal and the like. This clause does not apply to gas and liquid fuel burning appliances.</li></ul></callout></clause>